<L>__{interior old george's trailer night}
<A>__{old george sits hunched over a home made shortwave radio with a joint in his mouth. the postman sits beside him, listening as static pours from an old car speaker.}
<C>__{the postman}
<D>__{who do you talk to?}
<C>__{old george}
<D>__{not a soul in seven years of trying. but i will.}
<A>__{the postman steps to a telescope pointing up through a hole in the trailer ceiling.}
<C>__{old george}
<D>__{go ahead. take a look.}
<P>__{(offering joint)}
<D>__{want some?}
<C>__{the postman}
<D>__{no. no thanks. hey, don't let the kids see that.}
<A>__{george nods and goes on playing with the dials searching for a voice in the void. the postman focuses on the moon.}
<C>__{old george}
<D>__{i was an aerospace engineer. i helped design the galileo space station.}
<P>__{(scanning sky)}
<D>__{i dream it's orbiting earth forever. with a dozen human skeletons all grinning at each other. laughing at us down here.}
<A>__{there's an urgent knocking on the trailer door. ford appears.}
<C>__{the postman}
<D>__{what is it?}
<C>__{ford}
<D>__{it's red. he's overdue.}
<C>__{the postman}
<D>__{that makes five. all on southern routes.}
